To securely wire your ChatGPT integration into a backend and lay the foundation for uploading scripts and call recordings, here’s Step 1:

✅ Backend Endpoint: /api/ask-gpt

Here's an example using Node.js (Express):

js
// server/routes/ask-gpt.js
const express = require('express');
const fetch = require('node-fetch');
const router = express.Router();

router.post('/', async (req, res) => {
  const { prompt } = req.body;

  try {
    const response = await fetch('https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY}`,
      },
      body: JSON.stringify({
        model: 'gpt-4o',
        messages: [
          {
            role: 'system',
            content: 'You are a helpful assistant built into a CRM to assist with lead management, summaries, and communication.',
          },
          {
            role: 'user',
            content: prompt,
          },
        ],
      }),
    });

    const data = await response.json();
    res.json({ message: data.choices[0].message.content });
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(err);
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to contact OpenAI.' });
  }
});

module.exports = router;

Then in your main server file:

js
const express = require('express');
const bodyParser = require('body-parser');
require('dotenv').config();

const app = express();
app.use(bodyParser.json());

app.use('/api/ask-gpt', require('./routes/ask-gpt'));

const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3001;
app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`));

Here’s your Node.js (Express) backend code for the /api/upload-script route. It accepts uploaded audio or script files, transcribes audio using OpenAI Whisper API, and prepares the data for future training integration.

🔧 Backend: /api/upload-script

Install dependencies:

bash
npm install express multer node-fetch dotenv

Then create the route:

js
// server/routes/upload-script.js
const express = require('express');
const multer = require('multer');
const fetch = require('node-fetch');
const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');

const router = express.Router();
const upload = multer({ dest: 'uploads/' });

router.post('/', upload.single('file'), async (req, res) => {
  const filePath = req.file.path;
  const fileName = req.file.originalname;
  const fileMime = req.file.mimetype;

  try {
    // If it's audio, transcribe it
    if (fileMime.startsWith('audio/')) {
      const formData = new FormData();
      formData.append('file', fs.createReadStream(filePath));
      formData.append('model', 'whisper-1');

      const whisperRes = await fetch('https://api.openai.com/v1/audio/transcriptions', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {
          Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY}`,
        },
        body: formData,
      });

      const data = await whisperRes.json();
      fs.unlinkSync(filePath); // Clean up local file
      return res.json({ message: `Transcription complete: ${data.text}` });
    } else {
      // For now, just confirm the file is stored (text/PDF/etc.)
      fs.renameSync(filePath, path.join('uploads', fileName));
      return res.json({ message: `Script '${fileName}' uploaded successfully.` });
    }
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(err);
    res.status(500).json({ message: 'Upload or transcription failed.' });
  }
});

module.exports = router;

In your main server file (server.js or index.js):

js
const express = require('express');

Update your /api/ask-gpt route to:

js
// server/routes/ask-gpt.js
const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');
const express = require('express');
const fetch = require('node-fetch');
const router = express.Router();

router.post('/', async (req, res) => {
  const { prompt } = req.body;

  try {
    // Load context from recent training files
    const files = fs.readdirSync('./uploads')
      .filter(f => f.endsWith('.txt'))
      .slice(-3); // last 3 files
    const context = files.map(f => fs.readFileSync(`./uploads/${f}`, 'utf-8')).join('\n\n');

    const response = await fetch('https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY}`,
      },
      body: JSON.stringify({
        model: 'gpt-4o',
        messages: [
          {
            role: 'system',
            content: 'You are a helpful AI assistant for a CRM. Use the uploaded scripts to match the tone and approach of successful sales reps.',
          },
          {
            role: 'user',
            content: `Context from past sales scripts:\n${context}\n\nUser's question:\n${prompt}`,
          },
        ],
      }),
    });

    const data = await response.json();
    res.json({ message: data.choices[0].message.content });
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(err);
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to generate AI response.' });
  }
});

module.exports = router;

// models/Disposition.js
const { Sequelize, DataTypes } = require('sequelize');
const sequelize = require('../db');

const Disposition = sequelize.define('Disposition', {
  leadId: DataTypes.INTEGER,
  status: DataTypes.STRING, // 'no_answer', 'pickup', 'closed', 'presented', etc.
  callLength: DataTypes.FLOAT, // in minutes
}, {
  timestamps: true,
});

module.exports = Disposition;

🧠 API Route: /api/call-metrics

js
// routes/call-metrics.js
const express = require('express');
const router = express.Router();
const Disposition = require('../models/Disposition');
const { Op } = require('sequelize');

router.get('/', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const outboundCalls = await Disposition.count();
    const pickups = await Disposition.count({ where: { status: 'pickup' } });
    const closedDeals = await Disposition.count({ where: { status: 'closed' } });
    const optionsPresented = await Disposition.count({ where: { status: 'presented' } });

    const lengths = await Disposition.findAll({ attributes: ['callLength'] });
    const avgCallLength = (
      lengths.reduce((sum, d) => sum + (d.callLength || 0), 0) / (lengths.length || 1)
    ).toFixed(2);

    res.json({
      outboundCalls,
      pickups,
      avgCallLength: parseFloat(avgCallLength),
      optionsPresented,
      closedDeals,
    });
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Metrics error:', err);
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to calculate call metrics' });
  }
});

module.exports = router;

📁 /services/voiceService.js

js
const fs = require('fs');
const fetch = require('node-fetch');

async function generateVoiceMp3(text, outputFilePath) {
  const res = await fetch('https://api.openai.com/v1/audio/speech', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
      Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY}`,
      'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      model: 'tts-1',
      voice: 'nova', // or 'shimmer', 'echo', etc.
      input: text,
    }),
  });

  const dest = fs.createWriteStream(outputFilePath);
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    res.body.pipe(dest);
    res.body.on('error', reject);
    dest.on('finish', resolve);
  });
}

module.exports = { generateVoiceMp3 };

📄 DashboardLayout.jsx

jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

export default function DashboardLayout() {
  const [aiInput, setAiInput] = useState('');
  const [aiResponse, setAiResponse] = useState('');
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [metrics, setMetrics] = useState({
    outboundCalls: 0,
    pickups: 0,
    avgCallLength: 0,
    optionsPresented: 0,
    closedDeals: 0,
  });

  const handleAiRequest = async () => {    if (!aiInput.trim()) return;
    setLoading(true);
    setAiResponse('');
    try {
      const res = await fetch(`${import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL}/api/ask-gpt`, {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ prompt: aiInput }),
      });
      const data = await res.json();
      setAiResponse(data?.message || 'No response received.');
    } catch (err) {
      console.error('AI Request Error:', err);
      setAiResponse('Error contacting AI service.');
    }
    setLoading(false);
  };

  const fetchCallMetrics = async () => {
    try {
      const res = await fetch(`${import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL}/api/call-metrics`);
      const data = await res.json();
      setMetrics(data);
    } catch (err) {
      console.error('Failed to fetch call metrics:', err);
    }
  };

  useEffect(() => {
    fetchCallMetrics();
  }, []);

  return (
    <div className="p-6 space-y-4">
      <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold">DGVC CRM Dashboard</h1>
      <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <Metric title="Outbound Calls" value={metrics.outboundCalls} />
        <Metric title="Pickups" value={metrics.pickups} />
        <Metric title="Avg Call Length" value={metrics.avgCallLength} />
        <Metric title="Options Presented" value={metrics.optionsPresented} />
        <Metric title="Deals Closed" value={metrics.closedDeals} />
      </div>

      <section>
        <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold">AI Assistant</h2>
        <textarea
          className="w-full border p-2 rounded mb-2"
          value={aiInput}
          onChange={(e) => setAiInput(e.target.value)}
          placeholder="Ask something..."
        />
        <button onClick={handleAiRequest} className="bg-blue-700 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">
          {loading ? 'Thinking...' : 'Ask GPT'}
        </button>
        {aiResponse && <pre className="mt-2 bg-gray-100 p-2 rounded">{aiResponse}</pre>}
      </section>
    </div>
  );
}

function Metric({ title, value }) {
  return (
    <div className="bg-white shadow rounded p-4 text-center">
      <h3 className="text-gray-600 text-sm">{title}</h3>
      <p className="text-2xl font-semibold">{value ?? 'N/A'}</p>
    </div>
  );
}

📄 Use This for App.jsx (your CRM UI)

jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

export default function App() {
  const [aiInput, setAiInput] = useState('');
  const [aiResponse, setAiResponse] = useState('');
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);

  const handleAiRequest = async () => {
    if (!aiInput.trim()) return;
    setLoading(true);
    setAiResponse('');
    try {
      const res = await fetch(`${import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL}/api/ask-gpt`, {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ prompt: aiInput }),
      });
      const data = await res.json();
      setAiResponse(data?.message || 'No response received.');
    } catch (err) {
      console.error('AI Request Error:', err);
      setAiResponse('Error contacting AI service.');
    }
    setLoading(false);
  };

  return (
    <div className="p-6 space-y-4">
      <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold">DGVC CRM Dashboard</h1>
      <section>
        <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold">AI Assistant</h2>
        <textarea
          className="w-full border p-2 rounded mb-2"
          value={aiInput}
          onChange={(e) => setAiInput(e.target.value)}
          placeholder="Ask something..."
        />
        <button onClick={handleAiRequest} className="bg-blue-700 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">
          {loading ? 'Thinking...' : 'Ask GPT'}
        </button>
        {aiResponse && <pre className="mt-2 bg-gray-100 p-2 rounded">{aiResponse}</pre>}
      </section>
    </div>
  );
}
